# TEXT TAGGING PROTOCOL - CONDENSED

Tag text across 84 macro alignment variables. Output as JSON.

## NARRATIVE VOICE (10 variables)

**1.1 Point of View (POV)**
- FP = First Person ("I" narrator)
- SP = Second Person ("You" protagonist)
- TPL = Third Person Limited (one mind)
- TPO = Third Person Omniscient (all minds)

**1.2 Focalization**
- INT = Internal (limited to character perception)
- EXT = External (no mind access)
- ZERO = Zero (unlimited access)

**1.3 Narrator Reliability**
- REL = Reliable
- UNREL = Unreliable

**1.4 Temporal Distance**
- IMM = Immediate (present/recent)
- RETRO = Retrospective (distant past)

**1.5 Narrative Mode**
- MIM = Mimetic (showing/dialogue dominant)
- DIE = Diegetic (telling/summary dominant)
- BAL = Balanced

**1.6 Free Indirect Discourse**
- NONE = Not used
- SOME = Occasional use
- HEAVY = Frequent use

**1.7 Stream of Consciousness**
- NONE = Not used
- SOME = Occasional passages
- HEAVY = Dominant technique

**1.8 Character Revelation**
- DIR = Direct (narrator tells traits)
- IND = Indirect (actions/dialogue show traits)
- MIX = Mixed

**1.9 Narrative Intrusion**
- NONE = No commentary
- SOME = Occasional commentary
- HEAVY = Frequent commentary

**1.10 Voice Consistency**
- CONS = Consistent throughout
- VAR = Varies by section/chapter

## NARRATIVE STRUCTURE (10 variables)

**2.1 Chronology**
- LIN = Linear (chronological)
- ANA = Analeptic (flashbacks)
- PRO = Proleptic (flashforwards)
- FRAG = Fragmented (non-linear)

**2.2 Framing**
- NONE = No frame
- SIMPLE = Single frame story
- COMPLEX = Nested frames

**2.3 Plot Architecture**
- MONO = Single plot
- PARA = Parallel plots
- BRAID = Braided/interwoven
- EPISODIC = Episodic structure

**2.4 Pacing**
- FAST = Fast (action-heavy)
- SLOW = Slow (reflection-heavy)
- VAR = Variable

**2.5 Temporal Span**
- BRIEF = Hours/days
- MEDIUM = Weeks/months
- EXTENDED = Years/decades

**2.6 Beginning Type**
- MEDIAS = In medias res
- AB_OVO = Ab ovo (from beginning)
- FRAME = Framing device

**2.7 Ending Type**
- CLOSED = Resolved
- OPEN = Ambiguous/unresolved
- CIRCULAR = Returns to beginning

**2.8 Scene-to-Summary Ratio**
- SCENE = Scene-heavy (>60%)
- SUM = Summary-heavy (>60%)
- BAL = Balanced

**2.9 Chapter Structure**
- TRAD = Traditional chapters
- FRAG = Fragments/vignettes
- CONT = Continuous (no breaks)

**2.10 Causation**
- STRONG = Strong cause-effect
- WEAK = Loose connections
- THEME = Thematic unity

## RHETORICAL VOICE (8 variables)

**3.1 Dominant Tone**
- Free text description

**3.2 Register/Diction**
- FORM = Formal
- COLL = Colloquial
- POET = Poetic
- TECH = Technical

**3.3 Stance**
- OBJ = Objective (neutral)
- SUBJ = Subjective (personal)
- ADV = Advocative (persuasive)

**3.4 Ethos**
- STRONG = Strong credibility
- MOD = Moderate
- WEAK = Weak/questioned

**3.5 Pathos**
- STRONG = Heavy emotional appeal
- MOD = Moderate
- WEAK = Minimal emotion

**3.6 Logos**
- STRONG = Logic-driven
- MOD = Some reasoning
- WEAK = Minimal logic

**3.7 Irony**
- NONE = No irony
- VERB = Verbal irony
- SIT = Situational irony
- DRAM = Dramatic irony

**3.8 Figurative Density**
- LOW = Minimal figures
- MOD = Moderate use
- HIGH = Heavy use

## RHETORICAL STRUCTURE (6 variables)

**4.1 Alignment Type**
- CONF = Confirmatory (reinforces)
- TRANS = Transformative (challenges)
- AMB = Ambiguous

**4.2 Narrative-Rhetoric Relationship**
- TIGHT = Strong coupling
- LOOSE = Independent
- TENSION = Conflicting

**4.3 Primary Mechanism**
- PLOT = Plot-driven alignment
- CHAR = Character-driven
- THEME = Theme-driven
- STYLE = Style-driven

**4.4 Device Density**
- LOW = <5 devices per page
- MOD = 5-10 devices
- HIGH = >10 devices

**4.5 Device Distribution**
- EVEN = Evenly distributed
- CLUST = Clustered in sections
- PEAK = Peaks at climax

**4.6 Mediation Strategy**
- ACCUMULATION = Gradual buildup
- JUXTAPOSITION = Contrast/comparison
- REPETITION = Recurring patterns

## OUTPUT FORMAT

```json
{
  "narrative": {
    "voice": {
      "pov": "CODE",
      "pov_description": "brief explanation",
      "focalization": "CODE",
      "focalization_description": "brief explanation",
      "reliability": "CODE",
      "temporal_distance": "CODE",
      "mode_dominance": "CODE",
      "free_indirect": "CODE",
      "stream_consciousness": "CODE",
      "character_revelation": "CODE",
      "narrative_intrusion": "CODE",
      "voice_consistency": "CODE"
    },
    "structure": {
      "chronology": "CODE",
      "framing": "CODE",
      "plot_architecture": "CODE",
      "plot_architecture_description": "brief explanation",
      "pacing": "CODE",
      "temporal_span": "CODE",
      "beginning_type": "CODE",
      "ending_type": "CODE",
      "scene_summary_ratio": "CODE",
      "chapter_structure": "CODE",
      "causation": "CODE"
    }
  },
  "rhetoric": {
    "voice": {
      "tone": "description",
      "register": "CODE",
      "stance": "CODE",
      "ethos": "CODE",
      "pathos": "CODE",
      "logos": "CODE",
      "irony": "CODE",
      "figurative_density": "CODE"
    },
    "structure": {
      "alignment_type": "CODE",
      "narrative_rhetoric_relationship": "CODE",
      "primary_mechanism": "CODE",
      "device_density": "CODE",
      "device_distribution": "CODE",
      "mediation_strategy": "CODE"
    }
  },
  "device_mediation": {
    "summary": "How devices mediate alignment"
  }
}
```
